com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.api

Class SSRFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.api.SSRFactory

  • public final class SSRFactory
extends Object
    Helper class dealing with SSR creation.
    This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • createLoadCompound

        public static SSR createLoadCompound(SunriseCompoundType compoundType,
                                     String compoundInstanceName,
                                     String compoundObjName,
                                     SunriseCompoundMode compoundMode,
                                     String sprLayerName)
        Creates a SSR to load a compound instance.
        Parameters:
        compoundType - Compound type / compound category of the Sunrise compound.
        compoundInstanceName - Instance name of the compound, which should be created / loaded.
        compoundObjName - Object file name (containing the binaries to load the compound)
        compoundMode - Compound mode / task type (note: Currently, a Sunrise compound can be used either in kernel mode or in user mode).
        sprLayerName - SPR layer name (note: Currently, this parameter is optional for the compound instantiation - use an empty string, if you don't want to specify the SPR layer name.)
        Returns:
        the created SSR.

      • createSSR

        public static SSR createSSR(String functionName,
                            Object... args)
        Convenience method to create an SSR without having to think about classes of type ISerializableType.

        Because this method uses reflection to determine the message parameter types (which must be of an ISerializableType), it is not recommended to use this method where performance is important.

        Parameters:
        functionName - The name of the request (the ID of the SSR).
        args - The arguments for the procedure. If on argument is null, it is just omitted in the SSR.
        Returns:
        The corresponding SSR.

      • createDFEDataRequest

        public static SSR createDFEDataRequest(String deviceName,
                                       String observerName,
                                       String... dataNames)
        Creates a device request SSR with the given device and name as parameter.

        The result message of the SSR will contain the DFE values in the order in which they were specified. Furthermore, an additional (double-valued) parameter is appended as last value of the result message. This parameter contains a system timestamp.

        Parameters:
        deviceName - The name of the device.
        observerName - The name of the observer. Give an empty string for the default observer.
        dataNames - The name of the requested DFE-datas. Their values will be returned in the given order.
        Returns:
        The corresponding SSR.

      • createDFEDataRequest

        public static SSR createDFEDataRequest(String deviceName,
                                       String observerName,
                                       List<String> dataNames)
        Creates a device request SSR with the given device- and observer name as parameter.

        The result message of the SSR will contain the DFE values in the order in which they are contained in the given list.

        Furthermore, an additional (double-valued) parameter is appended as last value of the result message. This parameter contains a system timestamp.

        Parameters:
        deviceName - The name of the device.
        observerName - The name of the observer. Give an empty string for the default observer.
        dataNames - list of names of the requested DFE-data. Their values will be returned in the the same order as they are contained in the given list.
        Returns:
        The corresponding SSR.

      • createGetInverseKinematicsSSR

        public static SSR createGetInverseKinematicsSSR(String robotName,
                                                com.kuka.math.geometry.ITransformation transformation,
                                                com.kuka.geometry.LoadData loadData,
                                                String requestType)
        Creates a basic SSR for getting inverse kinematics.

        Different request type implementations have to call this method, get result and add their own parameters to the SSR before sending it.

        Parameters:
        robotName - name of the robot to calculate inverse kinematics
        transformation - root -> flange transformation
        loadData - load on the robot. Setting the load has no effect, if absolute accuracy is not activated for this kinematics
        requestType - type of inverse kinematics request
        Returns:
        SSR for calculating inverse kinematics

      • createGetForwardKinematicsSSR

        public static SSR createGetForwardKinematicsSSR(String robotName,
                                                com.kuka.device.common.JointPosition jointPosition,
                                                com.kuka.geometry.LoadData loadData,
                                                String requestType)
        Creates basic SSR for forward kinematics calculations.
        Parameters:
        robotName - name of the robot
        jointPosition - joint position of the robot for which forward kinematics should be calculated
        loadData - load data on the robot. Setting the load has no effect, if absolute accuracy is not activated for this kinematics
        requestType - type of the forward kinematics request
        Returns:
        basic SSR for forward kinematics calculations
